FILE: config.py
PURPOSE: Central configuration constants and mappings for JSON conversion

CONSTANTS:
- LANGUAGES: Maps language codes to language names (en→English, ar→Arabic, etc.)
- COUNTRIES: Maps country codes to country names (eg→Egypt, us→United States, etc.)
- VALID_PART_TYPES: List of allowed question part types (mcq, mrq, frq, oq, gapText, string, opinion, matching, counting, puzzle, input_box, frq_ai, gmrq)
- VALID_DIRECTIONS: Allowed ordering directions (vertical, horizontal)
- VALID_CHOICE_TYPES: Allowed choice types (key, distractor)
- VALID_CONSTRAINT_TYPES: Allowed input_box constraint types (decimal, integer)
- VALID_STRING_AI_TEMPLATE_IDS: List of valid string AI template IDs
- DEFAULT_SOURCE: Default source value ("human")
- GRID_SIZE_PATTERN: Regex pattern for counting question grid size (e.g., "5×4")
- ERROR_TYPES: Error type labels for reporting (PRE_VALIDATION, CONVERSION, POST_VALIDATION)
- EXCEL_COLUMNS: Column headers for Excel error reports (Filename, Question ID, Error Type, Error Message, Failed Field, Actual Value, Expected Format, Timestamp)

USAGE:
Imported by all other modules to ensure consistency in validation and conversion

